item.title: Need help fixing my cachedownloader please
item.dc:creator: @fic7ion fic7ion
item.description:
@fic7ion wrote:

[quote=“Justin Bieber, post:4, topic:551794”]There isn’t enough information in this question to help you.

What is the full error? All we can infer from “eNotFoundException: C:\Users\Maurice\WonderC” is that it’s probably a FileNotFoundException on a filename that we can’t even see.

Where is your code? How do we know you’re even pointing to the correct file if we can’t see the code that does it?[/quote]

I cannot copy the CMD’s code. I just re-downloaded the server & removed all the old files. Could someone perhaps help me set-up my cachedownloader? I could learn from that

Thanks in advance, Fic7ion.

[quote=“sk8rdude461, post:2, topic:551794”]It doesn’t look like you zipped the cache correctly.
Go into your cache (Where the main_file_cache.dat and .idx’s are), and select everything, then zip that.[/quote]
